  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.4,
      "text": "This is a livervox recording. All livervox recordings are in the public domain. For more information,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.86,
      "end": 9.8,
      "text": "or to volunteer, say visit the pervox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.18,
      "end": 13.9,
      "text": "ASOC's fables. The Shepherd's Boy and the Wolf.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.0,
      "end": 18.8,
      "text": "A Shepherd's Boy was tending his flock near a village and thought it would be great fun",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 18.8,
      "end": 23.64,
      "text": "to focus the villagers by pretending that a wolf was attacking the sheep. So he shouted",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.64,
      "end": 28.86,
      "text": "out, Wolf! Wolf! And when the people came running up, he'd have laughed at them for their pains.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.48,
      "end": 34.38,
      "text": "He did this more than once, and every time the villagers found they had been host, for",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.38,
      "end": 39.9,
      "text": "there was no wolf at all. At last, a wolf really did come and the boy cried, Wolf! Wolf!",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.78,
      "end": 45.42,
      "text": "As loud as he could, but the people were so used to hearing him call that they took no",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 45.42,
      "end": 50.68,
      "text": "notice of his cries for help. And so the wolf had it all his own way and killed off sheep",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 50.68,
      "end": 55.92,
      "text": "after sheep at his leisure. You cannot believe a liar even when he tells the truth.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 57.62,
      "end": 60.44,
      "text": "And of the Shepherd's Boy and the Wolf.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
